[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Goose version 125 is here and it\'s a big one. The headline feature is Mac OS sandboxing. Goose desktop now runs every command inside a native sandbox, restricting file system access, controlling network requests, and scoping write permissions. Your system'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stays protected even when goose runs code. Next up, the unified summon extension. We replace two separate systems, sub aents and skills, with one clean extension. Two tools, load and delegate. Simpler to understand, simpler'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to use. MCP extensions can now render rich interactive UI directly in the chat. Dashboards, forms, visualizations, all in line. Your conversations just got a lot more visual. You could already'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'edit recipes, but now you can change the model, provider, and extensions right from the guey. No more digging through YAML. Point. Click done. And for supply chain security, every release artifact now ships with signed SLSA Providence,'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so you can verify your binary came from the official repo. That\'s goosev 1.25.0. Upgrade today at block.github.io/goose. io/goose.'
